  "subject": "Docs: Modernise docs configuration for Python 3.13",
  "commit_message": "Docs: Modernise docs configuration for Python 3.13\n\nAlign documentation build configuration with the ONAP doc/ repository\nreference setup:\n\n- Remove setuptools upper bound (<81); upper-constraints pins to 69.0.3\n- Update Sphinx version floor to >=7.1.2 (from >=4.2.0)\n- Update sphinx-rtd-theme floor to >=2.0.0 (from >=1.0.0)\n- Add version bounds to sphinxcontrib-plantuml (>=0.27)\n- Add RTD deprecation context injection block to docs/conf.py\n- Remove obsolete formats: htmlzip from .readthedocs.yaml\n- Set basepython = python3.13 in root tox.ini (was python3)\n- Add upper-constraints to root tox.ini docs environment\n- Add -q (quiet) flag to sphinx-build commands\n- Enable docs-linkcheck in docs/tox.ini envlist with proper deps\n- Sync etc/requirements.txt with docs/requirements-docs.txt\n- Fix missing trailing newlines\n\nNote: -W (warnings-as-errors) is intentionally omitted from\nsphinx-build; the repository has ~112 pre-existing sphinx-needs\nlink_ref warnings that would need to be resolved first.\n\nIssue-ID: CIMAN-33\nChange-Id: Ia53491968dfc146d8fa31aa4ce42264f4aaa41c7\nSigned-off-by: Matthew Watkins <mwatkins@linuxfoundation.org>\n",
